Sierra Leone Posts Budget Surplus in June After Deficit in May, Bank Says

-- B y   S i l a s   G b a n d i a
-- 
2011-09-07T11:02:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/sierra-leone-posts-budget-surplus-in-june-after-deficit-in-may-bank-says.html
Sierra Leone posted a  budget surplus 
of 7.4 billion leones ($1.7 million) in June compared with a
deficit of 36.3 billion leones a month earlier, the central bank
said.  Revenue was 129.6 billion leones, the Freetown-based bank
said in an e-mailed report today.  Gross external reserves fell 1.9 percent to $344.6 million
in June from May, the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Silas Gbandia at 
